# Project Context

At session start, read **`.cursor/project-context.md`** when present. It summarizes:

- What the project is (multi-tenant fire department platform)
- Key constraints (tenant isolation, NERIS schema, no secrets in client/payloadJson, etc.)
- Where to find details: `docs/system_architecture.md`, `docs/data_model.md`, `docs/agent-execution-contract.md`, `docs/incident-lifecycle.md`, `docs/integrations.md`

When touching architecture, data, incidents, or external systems (CAD/NERIS/NEMSIS), read the relevant docs above and follow them. Give **beginner-friendly, step-by-step** directions and clear **do this now** vs **do this later** so the next agent can continue safely.
